\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces  Clustering of the gene families based on the rescaled min-max distances, when using all reference trees (top), only good reference trees (middle) or only random reference trees (bottom). We show several dimension reduction methods (PCA, Isomap, and Spectral Embedding). The colouring is based on k-means clustering with five clusters using all reference trees. }}{14}{figure.caption.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{figure007}{{7}{14}{Clustering of the gene families based on the rescaled min-max distances, when using all reference trees (top), only good reference trees (middle) or only random reference trees (bottom). We show several dimension reduction methods (PCA, Isomap, and Spectral Embedding). The colouring is based on k-means clustering with five clusters using all reference trees}{figure.caption.7}{}}
